<color=#3487e0>Extra Action</color>: Enables multiple actions within our turn.
<color=#3487e0>Taunt</color>: A unit affected by taunt will move towards the taunting unit and initiate an attack.
<color=#3487e0>Out of Control</color>: Units affected by this will move away from the source and enter standby.
<color=#3487e0>Team Attack</color>: If an enemy unit within this unit's or specified range is attacked by an ally, this unit will also attack that enemy once.
<color=#3487e0>Counterattack</color>: When attacked by an enemy within its attack range or specified area, it counterattacks once.
<color=#3487e0>Chase</color>: If an enemy unit attempts to move within this unit's attack range or designated area, it triggers one attack against that enemy.
<color=#3487e0>Surveillance</color>: Locks onto one enemy unit. If that unit attempts to move this turn, it immediately triggers an attack. This effect is removed if the surveilling unit is attacked.
<color=#3487e0>Conversion</color>: After dealing damage to an enemy target, recovers a specific percentage of that damage as health.
<color=#3487e0>Self-Destruction</color>: Upon reaching 0 health, deals damage to all units within a specified range.
<color=#3487e0>Self-Healing</color>: Recover HP of self at the end of the turn.
<color=#3487e0>Air Dominance</color>: If this unit is a flying unit, it is not affected by terrain effects while moving and is not protected by terrain effects when attacked.
<color=#3487e0>Electric Shock</color>: Units affected by Electric Shock deal damage to allied units within 1.5 tiles at the end of their action and apply Electric Shock to them.
<color=#3487e0>Movement Denied</color>: Units affected by Movement Denied cannot move but can perform basic attacks and active skills.
<color=#3487e0>Stun</color>: Units affected by Stun cannot take any action.
<color=#3487e0>Attack Denied</color>: Units affected by Attack Denied cannot do anything apart from moving or standing by.
<color=#3487e0>Hot Zone</color>: If a tile has a damaging effect, enemy units that enter it will lose a portion of their maximum HP at the end of their turn.
<color=#3487e0>Advance Warning</color>: The area indicated in this turn will be attacked next turn.
<color=#3487e0>Forcefield</color>: Damage applied to units with Forcefields will first deplete the Forcefield's Deflection Value.
<color=#3487e0>Raid</color>: If an enemy unit ends its movement within a certain range, launch 1 attack against it.
<color=#3487e0>Extreme Recovery</color>: If current HP is below 30%, restore HP to 100%. Can only be triggered once per battle
<color=#3487e0>Fragile Defense</color>: Units affected by <color=#3487e0>Vulnerable</color> take 50% more damage.
<color=#3487e0>Dual Boost</color>: Increases accuracy and damage dealt by 50%.
<color=#3487e0>Special Target</color>: Gain an 3 Confectance Index points when attacking this unit.
<color=#3487e0>Maintain Focus</color>: Enhances critical rate. The effect is lost upon taking any attack.
<color=#3487e0>Focused Offensive</color>: Increases damage dealt by 40% When HP is at or above 80% of maximum.
<color=#3487e0>Damage Burst</color>: Enhances damage dealt by 20%, stacking up to 5 times.
<color=#3487e0>Vision Increase I</color>: Increase accuracy of all allied units by 15%.
<color=#3487e0>Vision Increase II</color>: Increase accuracy of all allied units by 30%.
<color=#3487e0>Varjager Mark</color>: This unit is a member of the Varjagers. Eliminating them successfully will award an additional 2 points of Confectance Index.
<color=#3487e0>ELID Mark</color>: This unit is an ELID. Eliminating it successfully will award an additional 1 point of Confectance Index.
<color=#3487e0>PMC Mark</color>: This unit is a PMC mechanical unit. Eliminating it successfully will award an additional 3 points of Confectance Index..
<color=#3487e0>Powerful Unit Mark</color>: This unit is an unindeitified power combat unit. Eliminating it successfully will award an additional 10 points of Confectance Index.
<color=#3487e0>Unconfirmed Mark</color>: Information about this unit has exceeded the analysis limit.

<color=#3487e0>Precise Aim I</color>: Increase accuracy by 25% for self.
<color=#3487e0>Precise Aim II</color>: Increase accuracy by 50% for self.

<color=#3487e0>Mobile Support</color>: This unit will perform a <color=#3487e0>Team Attack</color> on enemy units within a 2-square radius, dealing damage equal to its own attack. This effect can trigger up to 3 times per turn.
<color=#3487e0>Dual Action</color>: If an enemy target is successfully eliminated, gain one <color=#3487e0>Extra Action</color>. This effect can trigger at most once per turn.
<color=#3487e0>Sustained Damage</color>: At the end of the turn, each stack of Continuous Damage causes the affected unit to lose % of their maximum HP as <r<kinetic>> damage. Stacks up to 5 times.
<color=#3487e0>United Boost</color>: If there are 2 or more allied units on the battlefield, increases own damage by 30%.
<color=#3487e0>Reactivation Pause</color>: Darture instantly returns to the battlefield but cannot perform any actions if his health is not at 100%.
<color=#3487e0>Mobility Evasion</color>: Increases own evasion by 50%; if attacked by any enemy unit within a 1.5 block radius, the evasion boost is only 25%.
<color=#3487e0>Global Breakthrough</color>: Increases damage dealt by all allied units on the battlefield by 50%.
<color=#3487e0>Brink of Death Lock</color>: Health will not fall below 1.
<color=#3487e0>Extra Command</color>: Allows multiple non-movement actions in our turn, with frequency depending on related skills or buff effects.

<color=#3487e0>Stability Break</color>: Mobility is reduced to 0, and no actions can be performed. During the duration of this effect, stability index is fixed at 0, and no new suppression trends can be established.
<color=#3487e0>Uncontrollable</color>: This unit is currently affected by Stun, Taunt, or Stability Break.

<color=#3487e0>ABoosted Support II</color>: Increase damage dealt by assists, boosting them to 50% of Krolik's attack.

<color=#3487e0>Firepower Expansion I</color>: Increase accuracy of self by 15%.

<color=#3487e0>Firepower Expansion II</color>: Increase accuracy of self by 25%.
<color=#3487e0>Directional Amplification II</color>: Increase attack of self equal to 25% of Nemesis·ETs' attack.
<color=#3487e0>Double Demolition</color>: After using Steel Rain, gain 1 instance of <color=#3487e0>Extra Action</color>. This effect can trigger up to 1 time per turn.
<color=#3487e0>Dual Boost</color>: Boosts your own accuracy by 15% and increases the damage you inflict by 15%
<color=#3487e0>Gathering Momentum</color>: For each stack of this effect held, it increases own dodge rate by 10% and boosts the damage dealt by Wind Slash by 5%

<color=#3487e0>Supplement Output I</color>: If there is an enemy unit within a 9-grid radius that is under attack by an ally, a Team Attack will be launched against this enemy unit. <color=#3487e0>Weakness Perception II</color>: When the current health is at least 80% of the maximum health, the damage inflicted by the self is boosted by 40%

<color=#3487e0>Mobility Assurance I</color>: Boosts your evasion by 15%
<color=#3487e0>Mobility Support II</color>: Increase dodge of self by 20%.

<color=#3487e0>Fragile Defense I</color>: Increase damage taken by 20%.
<color=#3487e0>Fragile Defense II</color>: Increase damage taken by 40%.

<color=#3487e0>Frost</color>: Apply <color=#3487e0>Frozen</color> to enemy units that stay on the affected tile at the end of their action. This effect lasts for <color=#f26c1c>2 turns</color>.
